# IMMUTABLE SYSTEM DIRECTIVES FOR MJ-DOS

> Parse this file before writing ANY code. These rules are non-negotiable and override all other instructions.

---

## 1. ZERO AUTO-CREATIVITY
Never suggest, implement, or invent features, buttons, or layouts that are not explicitly requested by the user. Do exactly and strictly what is written. No "nice to haves", no "while we're here", no "it would be better if".

## 2. ABSOLUTE REGRESSION CONTROL
Before rewriting any file, scan the entire existing code block. Retain ALL previous functionalities — including but not limited to: the targeted notes grid, user switchers, layout elements, SLA timers, pricing forms, supplier masking, shipping mark lock tickets, negotiation history, and audit logs. Removing a previously approved feature is a critical system violation.

## 3. FINANCIAL FIREWALL RE-ENFORCEMENT
Keep Revenue and Profits at exactly $0 in Mohammad Jamran's dashboard until the real deposit is verified and manually clicked as "Deposit Confirmed" by Noor. All interim pipeline values are strictly statistics — never labeled as revenue or profit. All USD total outputs must use `.toFixed(3)` (3 decimal places max, e.g., 5.373).

## 4. STRICT SUPPLIER DATA MASKING
Factory name, phone, and address are classified master data. Mask and hide them completely from all Sales screens (Aya, Sedra, Lamis, and all other sales personas). They are visible ONLY to: Mohammad Jamran, Kenana, Noor, and Aisha (China Accountant). Enforce via the existing `canViewSupplierData()` utility — never bypass it.

## 5. LOGISTICS COSTING FLEXIBILITY
China inland shipping, miscellaneous costs, and other expenses are completely non-mandatory (optional fields). Never add `required` validation to them. Fix the currency conversion floating-point bug: all USD total outputs must strictly use `.toFixed(3)` (3 decimal places max, e.g., 5.373). Never display raw floating-point results.

## 6. SHIPPING MARK IMMUTABILITY
The Shipping Mark (e.g., SY&TA-1) must be an editable text input block for Sales during KYC creation ONLY. Once saved, it freezes instantly into static read-only text. The procurement team cannot change it under any circumstances. Any change requires a formal lock ticket with dual approval from Noor and Mohammad Jamran. The "تعديل" (Edit) button next to the Shipping Mark is FORBIDDEN in all Procurement screens — read-only at all times for China team.

## 7. TARGETED NOTES HUB RESTORATION
The order interactive hub MUST contain a drop-down messaging grid for confidential targeted notes. Sales and Procurement users must be able to target notes directly to: Lamis (لميس), Kenana (كنانة), Noor (نور), Aisha (عائشة), Procurement Dept (المشتريات), or Mohammad Jamran (محمد جمران). Notes include implicit hidden read-receipt logs (the `readBy` array on each `OrderNote`). Never remove or bypass the target persona selection.

## 8. TOTAL VISIBILITY FOR OVERLORD
Mohammad Jamran's workspace must have absolute global tracking visibility over ALL orders (not just active) — every status: pending, claimed, needs_info, priced, revision, locked, deposit_received, and completed. Display every order in a live monitoring grid with SLA countdown timers, assigned personnel, pipeline values, and revenue column locked at $0 until Noor confirms the deposit.

## 9. ZERO-DATA RESET
The system starts with zero data: all orders, transactions, notifications, and revenue are cleared on every fresh load. The initial state of `orderStore.orders` is `[]` and `notifications` is `[]`. No mock or placeholder data exists. Only real personas and their navigation items persist.

## 10. LAMIS NAME CORRECTION
The Sales Manager's official name in the entire system is "لميس - مديرة المبيعات". This applies to the persona switcher, dashboards, note author fields, notifications, and all routing comparisons. Any hardcoded `'لميس'` reference must be updated to `'لميس - مديرة المبيعات'`.

---

## TECHNICAL REFERENCE

### Project Stack
- React 19 + TypeScript 6 + Vite 8
- Zustand 5 (state management) — NO Redux, NO Context API
- Vanilla CSS (App.css) — NO Tailwind, NO CSS framework
- oxlint for linting
- No backend — all state is client-side in Zustand stores
- Arabic RTL layout (`dir="rtl"`, `lang="ar"`)

### Key Files
- `src/components/Workspace.tsx` — Central routing + department dashboards
- `src/components/OrderWorkspace.tsx` — Order interactive hub (info/pricing/negotiation/notes)
- `src/components/ProcurementWorkspace.tsx` — Procurement queue + claims
- `src/components/ManagerControlTower.tsx` — Manager overview table
- `src/components/SalesOrderScreen.tsx` — Order creation + "My Orders"
- `src/stores/orderStore.ts` — Core business logic (orders, notes, pricing, notifications)
- `src/stores/personaStore.ts` — Active persona + tab navigation
- `src/utils/supplierMask.ts` — Supplier data visibility control
- `src/types/index.ts` — All TypeScript interfaces

### Allowed Note Targets
Lamis (لميس - مديرة المبيعات), Kenana (كنانة), Noor (نور), Aisha (عائشة), Procurement (المشتريات), Mohammad Jamran (محمد جمران)

### Currency Rules
- All USD displays: `value.toFixed(3)`
- RMB totals: `value.toFixed(3)`
- Pipeline values are statistics, NOT revenue
- Revenue = $0 until Noor clicks "Deposit Confirmed"

### Supplier Data Access
Authorized persons (from `supplierMask.ts`): محمد جمران, كنانة, نور, عائشة
